# Select supported scopes

OpenID Connect (OIDC) scopes are identifiers your application uses during authentication to authorise access to a user's details, such as an email address.

Each scope returns a set of user attributes, which OIDC calls ‘claims’.

GOV.UK Sign in currently supports 3 scopes and you’ll need to choose which of these scopes your service will use. You’ll provide the scopes when you make your authorisation request.

`openid` is the only scope you must include. You can choose to include other scopes for your authorisation request depending on the user attributes your service needs.

